data.name: AuthenticationRequest
desc: An error specifying lack of correct authentication data (e.g., to log into an account).

properties.name: Account
desc: If HasAccount is false, this member should be ignored.

properties.name: Diagnostic
desc: Any diagnostic message about the failure to log in (if applicable; it will typically be an English phrase or sentence).

properties.name: HasAccount
desc: Specifies if the authentication involves an \"account\" (as can be the case for FTP).

properties.name: HasPassword
desc: Specifies if the authentication involves a \"password\" (as is almost always the case).

properties.name: HasRealm
desc: Specifies if the authentication involves a \"realm\" (as can be the case for HTTP).

properties.name: HasUserName
desc: Specifies if the authentication involves a \"user name\" (as is almost always the case).

properties.name: Password
desc: If HasPassword is false, this member should be ignored.

properties.name: Realm
desc: If HasRealm is false, this member should be ignored.

properties.name: ServerName
desc: The name of the server (if applicable).

properties.name: UserName
desc: If HasUserName is false, this member should be ignored.
